<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_igær" xml:lang="os"><form type="lemma"><orth>igær</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>печень</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>liver</q></cit></sense><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_igær." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>æxsyry cady īw x˳y ī, æmæ myn ūj igærtæ ærxæssūt, ændæra æz amælʒynæn</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>в молочном озере есть один кабан, достаньте мне его печень, а не то я умру</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>there is a boar in the milk lake, bring me its liver, or else I will die</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>52</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>de ‘gær fækkalaj, Satana!</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>чтобы рассыпалась твоя печень (?), Шатана!</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>may your liver crumble (?), Satana!</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 45</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><re><form type="lemma"><orth>de ‘gær fækalaj</orth></form><note type="comment" xml:lang="">— </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="">— </note></re><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>æxsyry cady īw x˳y ī, æmæ myn ūj igærtæ ærxæssūt, ændæra æz amælʒynæn</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>в молочном озере есть один кабан, достаньте мне его печень, а не то я умру</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>there is a boar in the milk lake, bring me its liver, or else I will die</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>52</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>de ‘gær fækkalaj, Satana!</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>чтобы рассыпалась твоя печень (?), Шатана!</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>may your liver crumble (?), Satana!</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 45</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Как и другие основные анатомические термины, является общеиндоевропейским словом. Существовали два варианта основы: *%iyek''r-%i и *%iyek''n-%i. Осетинская форма возводится к др.иран. *%iyakar-%i, и.е. *%iyek''r-%i. Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>jigar</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/><w>jerk</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/><w>jagar</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"><lang/><w>уēγən (← *yaxna)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/><w>yina</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>gyagarrä</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>yākar-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>yakṛt</w></mentioned>, родительный падеж %iyaknah%i, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/><w>jecur</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/><w>ήπαρ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/><w>jēknos</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lv"><lang/><w>aknas</w></mentioned> и пр. (<bibl corresp="#ref_Pokorny"><biblScope>504</biblScope></bibl>). Начальный %ii%i в %iigær%i — из %iуа%i, как <xr><ref target="#entry_i"/></xr> (артикль) из %iya%i, <xr><ref target="#entry_izæd"/></xr> д. из %iyazata%i.%n<bibl corresp="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"><biblScope>II 67, 90, III 160; Gr. 17</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl corresp="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."><biblScope>41</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl corresp="#ref_ОЯФ_I"><biblScope>18</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It is a Proto-Indo-European word, as well as other general anatomical terms. Two stem variants existed: *%iyek''r-%i and *%iyek''n-%i. The Ossetic form is traced to Old Iranian *%iyakar-%i, Indo-European *%iyek''r-%i. Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>jigar</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/><w>jerk</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/><w>jagar</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"><lang/><w>уēγən (← *yaxna)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/><w>yina</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>gyagarrä</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>yākar-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>yakṛt</w></mentioned>, genitive case %iyaknah%i, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/><w>jecur</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/><w>ήπαρ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/><w>jēknos</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lv"><lang/><w>aknas</w></mentioned> etc. (<bibl corresp="#ref_Pokorny"><biblScope>504</biblScope></bibl>). The initial %ii%i in %iigær%i — from %iуа%i, like <xr><ref target="#entry_i"/></xr> (the article) from %iya%i, <xr><ref target="#entry_izæd"/></xr> Digor from %iyazata%i.%n<bibl corresp="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"><biblScope>II 67, 90, III 160; Gr. 17</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl corresp="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."><biblScope>41</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl corresp="#ref_ОЯФ_I"><biblScope>18</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry>